WEBVTT

00:01.130 --> 00:02.995
PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:03.000 --> 00:05.025
DUNCAN?

00:05.030 --> 00:06.691
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
HOW OFI'EN YOU'D VISITED
MEG SINCE THE ACCIDENT?

00:06.700 --> 00:08.292
Celeste: WHAT DID YOU SAY
TO DUNCAN?

00:08.300 --> 00:10.302
LET'S START WITH
WHAT I DIDN'T TELL HIM.

00:10.310 --> 00:12.175
I DIDN'T TELL HIM

00:12.180 --> 00:14.034
THAT HIS MOTHER DROVE MY MOTHER
OUT OF TOWN.

00:14.040 --> 00:17.271
THE NIGHT FELIX GOT KILLED, DID
YOU SEE WHO CALLED THE COPS?
NO, MAN.

00:17.280 --> 00:18.747
I'M GETTING
TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS.

00:18.750 --> 00:21.639
WHAT HAPPENED TO FELIX?
I CAN'T REMEMBER, OKAY?

00:23.050 --> 00:24.187
[ RINGS ]

00:24.190 --> 00:26.010
IS IT DONE?

00:26.020 --> 00:29.751
YOU HAVE NO IDEA THE HELL
YOU JUST BROUGHT ON YOURSELF.

00:29.760 --> 00:33.298
Hauser: SINCE YOU ALL
HAD SUCH A RAUCOUS GOOD TIME

00:33.300 --> 00:35.029
WITH VENEREAL DISEASES,

00:35.030 --> 00:39.137
I'M SURE YOU'LL BE THRILLED
WITH PHASE TWO OF SEX ED.

00:39.140 --> 00:42.029
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN...

00:42.040 --> 00:45.498
WELCOME TO PARENTHOOD.

00:46.180 --> 00:48.603
SO THAT'S
WHERE BABIES COME FROM.

00:48.610 --> 00:53.479
FOR THE NEXT FIVE DAYS,
YOU MOMS AND DADS WILL TEAM UP

00:53.480 --> 00:57.940
AND CARE FOR YOUR VERY OWN
BABY THIN K-IT-OVER.

00:57.950 --> 01:00.282
[ BABY CRYING ]

01:00.290 --> 01:02.520
SOME PARENTING TIPS.

01:02.530 --> 01:06.091
YOUR BABIES HAVE
VERY SOPHISTICATED SENSORS.

01:06.100 --> 01:09.297
THEY KNOW WHEN
THEY WANT TO BE HELD...

01:09.300 --> 01:13.168
AND WHEN THEY WANT A BOTTLE.

01:13.170 --> 01:14.831
[ CRYING STOPS ]

01:14.840 --> 01:17.206
MOST IMPORTANTLY, YOUR BABIES
HAVE VERY GOOD MEMORIES --

01:17.210 --> 01:19.201
OR RATHER, MEMORY CHIPS.

01:19.210 --> 01:22.247
SO, IF YOU'RE LOOKING
TO PASS THIS CLASS,

01:22.250 --> 01:26.038
I'D GIVE JUNIOR
SOME SERIOUS TLC.

01:26.050 --> 01:29.417
NOW, FIND A PARTNER,
PICK A BABY.

01:30.320 --> 01:34.689
OH, AREN'T WE SUPPOSED TO HAVE
A SHOT OF TEQUILA FIRST?

01:39.300 --> 01:43.418
PICK A GOOD 'UN, HONEY.
I GOT TO GO SEE THE MAN.

01:46.740 --> 01:50.733
WHAT DO YOU GOT FOR ME --
S.A.T. CHEATING SCAM,

01:50.740 --> 01:53.129
TOILET CAM
IN THE GIRLS' LOCKER ROOM,

01:53.140 --> 01:56.303
A STICKY DIVORCE,
PERHAPS?

01:56.310 --> 01:59.143
I NEED FOR YOU TO OPEN UP
YOUR PURSE, VERONICA.

01:59.150 --> 02:00.640
HAND OVER YOUR KEYS.

02:07.360 --> 02:09.453
ALL YOUR KEYS.

02:26.380 --> 02:28.109
I CAN EXPLAIN THAT.

02:28.110 --> 02:29.509
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

02:29.510 --> 02:31.603
THE DISTRICT '5 PUT IN
A SECURITY SYSTEM

02:31.610 --> 02:34.374
THAT KEEPS TRACK
OF ALL AFTER-HOURS VISITORS.

02:34.380 --> 02:36.382
I DON'T SEE
ANY CAMERAS HERE.

02:36.390 --> 02:39.041
THERE'S NO WAY YOU CAN PROVE
THAT I BROKE IN.

02:39.050 --> 02:41.587
HOW ELSE COULD YOU HAVE GOTTEN
THE DRUG TESTING RESULTS?

02:41.590 --> 02:43.626
THE FAKED
DRUG TEST RESULTS?

02:43.630 --> 02:45.655
LET ME WALK YOU
THROUGH IT.

02:45.660 --> 02:48.629
USUALLY WHEN I SAVE YOUR BUTT,
I START BY --

02:48.630 --> 02:50.461
WHAT ELSE HAVE YOU STOLEN
FROM MY SCHOOL?

02:50.470 --> 02:52.392
I CAN'T IMAGINE
THAT ALL OF THESE KEYS

02:52.400 --> 02:54.061
BELONG TO YOUR PROPERTY.

02:54.070 --> 02:56.868
FOR INSTANCE,
WHAT'S THIS ONE FOR?

02:56.870 --> 02:58.531
THAT ONE? LET'S SEE.

02:58.540 --> 03:04.172
THAT ONE OPENS A DuraGuard FILE
SAFE MANUFACTURED PRIOR TO 1990.

03:04.180 --> 03:06.341
AND, UH, THIS ONE?

03:06.350 --> 03:08.614
FITS ANY VESPA SCOOTER.

03:09.450 --> 03:11.418
WHAT?
I LIKE TO COME PREPARED.

03:11.420 --> 03:13.615
IN THAT CASE, PREPARE YOURSELF
FOR A SUSPENSION.

03:13.620 --> 03:15.315
YOU BROKE INTO
MY FILING CABINET.

03:15.320 --> 03:18.323
THAT'S POSSIBLY EVEN GROUNDS
FOR THE SHERIFF'S INVOLVEMENT.

03:18.330 --> 03:20.924
IF YOU SUSPEND ME,
I WON'T BE ELIGIBLE FOR --

03:20.930 --> 03:22.227
THE KANE SCHOLARSHIP.

03:22.230 --> 03:24.289
YES, I'M AWARE OF BOTH
YOUR ACADEMIC RECORD

03:24.300 --> 03:25.824
AND YOUR
FINANCIAL SITUATION.

03:25.830 --> 03:31.359
I MIGHT BE INCLINED
TO LET YOU OFF WITH DETENTION.

03:31.370 --> 03:33.634
FINE, DETENTION.
I'LL TAKE IT.

03:38.010 --> 03:39.978
EXCUSE ME, MAC?

03:39.980 --> 03:41.072
MAC?

03:41.080 --> 03:42.479
OH, WERE YOU
TALKING TO ME?

03:42.490 --> 03:44.378
YEAH, I WAS,
ACTUALLY.

03:44.390 --> 03:47.314
UM, I WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD HIRE YOU.

03:47.320 --> 03:48.514
TO DO WHAT?

03:48.520 --> 03:50.226
WELL, I NEED
A DOMAIN REGISTERED

03:50.230 --> 03:52.118
AND AN ONLINE IDENTITY FOR
MY COMPANY, PHOENIX LAND TRUST.

03:52.130 --> 03:55.554
I WOULD ALSO NEED YOU TO DESIGN
A LOGO FOR MY LETTERHEAD.

03:55.560 --> 03:59.838
YOU KNOW, I-I-I'M HAPPY TO MATCH
WHATEVER YOUR GOING RATE IS.

03:59.840 --> 04:03.139
I NEED THE WORK
TO BE FORTUNE 500 CALIBER.

04:03.140 --> 04:06.632
LOOK, I'LL HELP YOU GET
YOUR COMPANY UP AND RUNNING,

04:06.640 --> 04:08.699
BUT BASICALLY
YOU'RE HIRING ME

04:08.710 --> 04:11.679
TO DO YOUR HOMEWORK
FOR YOU, RIGHT?

04:11.680 --> 04:12.442
UM...

04:12.450 --> 04:14.714
[ CHUCKLES ]
RIGHT.

04:14.720 --> 04:17.041
Alan:
SOME OTHER EXCITING NEWS --
NEPTUNE PLAYERS

04:17.050 --> 04:20.281
WILL BE HOLDING OPEN AUDITION
FOR "HAMLET" ALL WEEK,

04:20.290 --> 04:21.917
AND I AM ESPECIALLY PROUD

04:21.920 --> 04:24.525
TO ANNOUNCE THIS YEAR'S
SPECIAL CELEBRITY DIRECTOR --

04:24.530 --> 04:27.954
TELEVISION AND SCREEN STAR,
NOT TO MENTION NHS ALUM,

04:27.960 --> 04:29.689
MISS TRINA ECHOLLS.

04:29.700 --> 04:32.021
Veronica: PRINCIPAL MOOREHEAD,
YOU OLD STAR STROKER.

04:32.030 --> 04:34.464
IF LOGAN'S SISTER
IS BACK IN NEPTUNE,

04:34.470 --> 04:36.609
THAT MUST MEAN
SHE WAS THE FIRST ONE

04:36.610 --> 04:39.135
BOOTED OFF "THE SURREAL LIFE"
THIS SEASON.

04:39.140 --> 04:40.676
VERONICA...

04:40.680 --> 04:42.739
YOU ARE AWARE
THAT SCHOOL ISN'T OVER YET?

04:42.750 --> 04:44.843
BUT DETENTION
WAS JUST SO CLOSE.

04:44.850 --> 04:48.411
I CONVINCED MY 7th-PERIOD
TEACHER TO LET ME OUT EARLY.

04:48.420 --> 04:51.742
FOLLOW ME, THEN.
GOT A LITTLE PROJECT FOR YOU.

04:53.520 --> 04:56.318
THE JANITOR HAD A DOLLY ACCIDENT
LAST WEEK

04:56.330 --> 04:58.321
MOVING
THE PERMANENT RECORDS.

04:58.330 --> 04:59.524
YOUR SENTENCE IS UP

04:59.530 --> 05:01.657
WHEN EACH
OF THESE FILES

05:01.660 --> 05:05.892
FINDS ITS WAY ALPHABETICALLY
INTO THAT CABINET.

05:07.640 --> 05:10.336
AND I CAN'T
USE MAGIC, RIGHT?

05:27.290 --> 05:29.087
MY MOM'S PERMANENT RECORD?

05:29.090 --> 05:31.888
SIX MONTHS AGO SHE VANISHED
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,

05:31.890 --> 05:34.927
BUT I GUESS WE ALL LEAVE
A LITTLE SOMETHING BEHIND.

05:34.930 --> 05:37.091
MOM DIDN'T TALK ABOUT
HER NEPTUNE DAYS VERY OFTEN.

05:37.100 --> 05:39.432
BUT BACK BEFORE SHE STARTED
DRINKING, SHE TOLD ME

05:39.440 --> 05:42.568
THAT HIGH SCHOOL IS SOMETHING
YOU HAD TO GET THROUGH.

05:42.570 --> 05:43.605
I KNEW WHAT SHE MEANT.

05:43.610 --> 05:45.362
I ALWAYS LIKED IMAGINING

05:45.370 --> 05:48.430
THAT I WOULD'VE GOTTEN ALONG
WITH LIANNE AS A TEENAGER,

05:48.440 --> 05:49.976
EVEN LONG AFTER
LIANNE THE ADULT

05:49.980 --> 05:52.619
FAILED TO MEET
OR EXCEED EXPECTATIONS.

05:52.620 --> 05:54.713
"LIANNE REYNOLDS --
SUSPENDED THREE DAYS

05:54.720 --> 05:57.416
"FOR SPREADING FALSE
AND MALICIOUS RUMORS

05:57.420 --> 05:59.888
CONCERNING ANOTHER STUDENT."

06:01.920 --> 06:04.150
"LIANNE REYNOLDS APPEARED
AT A DISCIPLINARY HEARING

06:04.160 --> 06:08.096
ALONG WITH FELLOW STUDENT
DEBORAH PHILIPINA DRUMMOND."

06:08.100 --> 06:10.819
HUH. I WONDER
IF SHE'S ANY RELATION

06:10.830 --> 06:12.764
TO DEBORAH PHILIPINA HAUSER.

06:12.770 --> 06:14.863
THIS IS GONNA TAKE YOU
A VERY LONG TIME

06:14.870 --> 06:18.237
IF YOU PLAN TO READ
EACH INDIVIDUALLY.

06:18.240 --> 06:19.502
I WAS JUST --

06:19.510 --> 06:21.273
SNOOPING THROUGH
SCHOOL PROPERTY.

06:21.280 --> 06:23.703
ISN'T THAT WHAT LANDED YOU
HERE IN DETENTION?

06:24.750 --> 06:26.445
BACK TO WORK, VERONICA.

06:34.360 --> 06:36.624
[ GRINDING ]

06:41.960 --> 06:46.226
HEY, YOU TRIPPED
THE DAMN BREAKER AGAIN, BERTO!

06:46.230 --> 06:48.039
YOU HEAR ME, MAN?!

06:52.440 --> 06:54.408
[ WHISTLES ]

06:56.240 --> 06:58.777
I HEARD YOUR LIGHTS WERE OUT.

06:59.650 --> 07:01.572
EVER HEAR OF GENETICS, KID?

07:01.580 --> 07:03.013
THANKS TO YOUR GRANDMA,

07:03.020 --> 07:06.046
I'VE GOT A 50/50 SHOT
AT BECOMING AN ALKY.

07:06.050 --> 07:10.658
GUESS THAT MAKES YOUR ODDS
1-IN-4, WHICH ISN'T SO BAD.

07:10.660 --> 07:14.551
OH, AND THERE'S ALSO
THIS LATENT MEAN-GIRL GENE.

07:14.560 --> 07:17.768
YOU'RE LUCKY
YOU'RE MADE OUT OF PLASTIC.

07:17.770 --> 07:20.568
HEY, MRS. HAUSER,
DO YOU HAVE A SEC?

07:20.570 --> 07:22.094
I HAVEN'T HAD
MY COFFEE.

07:22.100 --> 07:25.103
INTRUDE ON MY PERSONAL TIME
AT YOUR OWN RISK.

07:25.110 --> 07:28.671
YOU USED TO BE FRIENDS
WITH MY MOM, LIANNE REYNOLDS?

07:28.680 --> 07:31.444
YOU WERE
IN THE SAME CLASS?

07:31.450 --> 07:32.917
I KNEW YOUR MOTHER.

07:32.920 --> 07:37.084
WELL ENOUGH TO GET SUSPENDED
TOGETHER SENIOR YEAR.

07:37.090 --> 07:39.957
WHY WOULD YOU DIG UP
AN UGLY STORY LIKE THAT?

07:39.960 --> 07:41.882
DISCOVERING THAT YOUR MOM
AND YOUR TEACHER

07:41.890 --> 07:44.552
WERE SUSPENDED FOR SPREADING
A FALSE AND MALICIOUS RUMOR --

07:44.560 --> 07:46.494
WHO WOULDN'T WANT
TO KNOW MORE ABOUT THAT?

07:46.500 --> 07:48.650
IT'S NOT A JUICY STORY,
VERONICA.

07:48.660 --> 07:50.127
IT'S AN EMBARRASSMENT.

07:50.130 --> 07:53.293
I'M ASHAMED I EVEN LISTENED
TO LIANNE'S GOSSIP,

07:53.300 --> 07:54.836
LET ALONE REPEAT IT.

07:54.840 --> 07:56.865
I DIDN'T UNDERSTAND
THE CONSEQUENCES.

07:56.870 --> 07:58.508
A LOT OF PEOPLE
GOT HURT

07:58.510 --> 08:02.037
BECAUSE YOUR MOTHER JUST
COULDN'T KEEP HER MOUTH SHUT.

08:02.040 --> 08:05.942
MAYBE YOU CAN LEARN
FROM HER MISTAKE.

08:09.280 --> 08:11.214
[ BABY CRYING ]

08:28.300 --> 08:30.109
THERE YOU GO, KID.

08:30.110 --> 08:34.877
HERE'S LIFE LESSON NUMBER ONE --
WHAT GOES AROUND, COMES AROUND.

08:34.880 --> 08:38.873
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

08:38.880 --> 08:44.238
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

08:44.890 --> 08:47.017
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR *

08:47.020 --> 08:49.557
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

08:49.560 --> 08:53.052
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN *

08:53.060 --> 08:57.895
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS
A LONG TIME AGO *

08:57.900 --> 09:00.164
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

09:00.170 --> 09:03.799
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

09:12.050 --> 09:17.147
YOU'VE BEEN WORKING HERE
FOR WHAT, LIKE, EVER?

09:17.150 --> 09:20.381
ANY IDEA WHAT MY MOM DID
HER SENIOR YEAR

09:20.390 --> 09:22.278
TO GET HERSELF
SUSPENDED?

09:22.290 --> 09:24.326
LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT --
YOU WANT FOLLOW-UP

09:24.330 --> 09:27.151
ON WHAT I EXPLICITLY FORBADE YOU
FROM DOING YESTERDAY?

09:27.160 --> 09:29.299
UM...YES.

09:29.300 --> 09:32.167
MORE ALPHABETIZING,
LESS COLD-CASING.

09:32.170 --> 09:34.161
[ SIGHS ]

09:37.270 --> 09:41.309
BACK THEN
I WAS A YOUNG SCIENCE TEACHER.

09:41.310 --> 09:43.949
I WOULD HAVE NO IDEA.
DIDN'T YOU READ THE REPORT?

09:43.950 --> 09:46.145
YEAH, BUT THEY BLACKED
ALL THE GOOD STUFF OUT.

09:46.150 --> 09:47.549
HMM.

09:47.550 --> 09:49.882
WHO ELSE WAS HERE
IN 1980?

09:49.890 --> 09:51.448
WHAT?

09:51.450 --> 09:54.010
I'M JUST TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT KIND OF PERSON MY MOM WAS.

09:54.990 --> 09:56.548
MRS. HAUSER
WAS A STUDENT.

09:56.560 --> 09:58.619
MR. MOOREHEAD
WAS THE VICE PRINCIPAL.

09:58.630 --> 10:01.849
MARY MOONEY
WAS A STUDENT.

10:01.860 --> 10:04.897
I THINK THAT'S IT,
THE ENTIRE LIST.

10:04.900 --> 10:07.130
MARY MOONEY?
WHO'S THAT?

10:08.400 --> 10:10.709
EXCUSE ME, MARY?

10:10.710 --> 10:11.961
MARY MOONEY?

10:11.970 --> 10:14.530
Boy: YOU CAN ASK
AS LOUD AS YOU WANT.

10:14.540 --> 10:15.905
LUNCH LADY
DOES NOT TALK.

10:15.910 --> 10:18.174
SHE'S, LIKE, RETARDED
OR DEAF OR SOMETHING.

10:18.180 --> 10:21.217
MOM LEARNED TO SIGN BECAUSE
SHE HAD AN AUNT WHO WAS DEAF.

10:21.220 --> 10:24.747
SHE TAUGHT ME THE ALPHABET,
BUT THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

10:24.750 --> 10:26.308
EXCUSE ME.

10:26.320 --> 10:27.787
DID YOU KNOW...

10:27.790 --> 10:32.329
L-I-A-N-N-E

10:32.330 --> 10:36.664
R-E-Y-O-N-L-D-S?

10:39.840 --> 10:41.865
ALAS, IT SEEMS
THAT SIGN LANGUAGE

10:41.870 --> 10:44.703
ISN'T AT ALL
LIKE RIDING A BICYCLE.

10:46.610 --> 10:49.329
I'M SORRY.
CAN YOU GO SLOWER?

10:49.340 --> 10:52.741
LIANNE WAS A...

10:52.750 --> 10:54.968
FIEND?

10:56.550 --> 10:57.812
MY MOM, THE FIEND.

10:57.820 --> 11:00.880
TELL ME SOMETHING
I DON'T KNOW.

11:05.960 --> 11:07.188
PRINCIPAL MOOREHEAD.

11:07.200 --> 11:08.690
VERONICA.

11:08.700 --> 11:12.192
I SEE THAT MR. CLEMMONS IS
FAILING IN HIS PRIME DIRECTIVE.

11:12.200 --> 11:13.189
WHAT'S THAT?

11:13.200 --> 11:14.895
KEEPING YOU
OUT OF MY FACE.

11:14.900 --> 11:16.868
MIND IF WE WALK
AND TALK?

11:16.870 --> 11:19.464
YOU WERE VICE PRINCIPAL HERE
IN 1980.

11:19.470 --> 11:20.835
INDEED, I WAS.

11:20.840 --> 11:23.240
AND YOU SUSPENDED MY MOM
FOR SPREADING A FALSE

11:23.250 --> 11:25.502
AND MALICIOUS RUMOR
ABOUT ANOTHER STUDENT.

11:25.510 --> 11:28.479
THAT SOUNDS LIKE ME.
WHAT WAS YOUR MOM'S NAME?

11:28.480 --> 11:29.447
LIANNE REYNOLDS.

11:29.450 --> 11:30.849
[ WHISTLES ]

11:30.850 --> 11:34.286
WELL, UH, I SAW A GREAT DEAL
OF YOUR MOTHER,

11:34.290 --> 11:35.450
AS A MATTER OF FACT.

11:35.460 --> 11:37.758
DO YOU REMEMBER
WHY SHE WAS SUSPENDED?

11:37.760 --> 11:39.796
WHAT DID SHE SAY
THAT WAS SO AWFUL?

11:39.800 --> 11:41.427
WELL, OF COURSE, I DON'T,
VERONICA.

11:41.430 --> 11:43.591
BUT EVEN IF I DID,
WHY WOULD I WANT TO REPEAT IT?

11:43.600 --> 11:47.138
I'M SURE YOUR MOM TURNED INTO
A TERRIFIC PERSON.

11:47.140 --> 11:51.429
BUT DURING THE TIME SHE
WAS HERE, LIANNE WAS RATHER...

11:51.440 --> 11:53.237
VICIOUS.

11:59.410 --> 12:01.549
[ GASPS ] VERONICA?

12:01.550 --> 12:03.211
AND YOU, ALAN.

12:03.220 --> 12:05.484
HOW'S MY
FAVORITE PRINCIPAL?

12:05.490 --> 12:06.752
TAKE FIVE.

12:06.760 --> 12:08.011
OH.

12:08.860 --> 12:11.158
OH, ISN'T HE
A BIG OLD TEDDY BEAR?

12:11.160 --> 12:14.596
WELL, TRINA, IT'S GOOD
TO HAVE YOU BACK HERE.

12:14.600 --> 12:17.068
AND YOU LOOK...

12:18.300 --> 12:19.267
. . . FANTASTIC.

12:19.270 --> 12:22.034
THAT LOOK IS SO GREAT.
J'ADORE.

12:22.040 --> 12:23.962
SO, HOW HAVE YOU BEEN?

12:23.970 --> 12:26.109
I MEAN, ASIDE FROM THAT WHOLE
MESS WITH DAD AND ALL.

12:26.110 --> 12:28.499
WHAT, THAT?
IT'S WATER UNDER THE BRIDGE.

12:28.510 --> 12:31.104
GREAT. I'VE REALLY
BEEN MEANING TO CALL YOU.

12:31.110 --> 12:34.443
THERE HAS BEEN SOME SUPER
EXCITING NEWS WITH THE PROJECT.

12:34.450 --> 12:37.248
THREE WORDS --
EVAN RACHEL WOOD.

12:37.250 --> 12:38.478
OKAY.

12:38.490 --> 12:41.482
SHE'S GONNA PLAY YOU
IN "THE AARON ECHOLLS STORY."

12:41.490 --> 12:44.357
NAME CHANGED SINCE YOU
WON'T SIGN THE RELEASE FORMS.

12:44.360 --> 12:45.987
IT'S SUCH A GREAT PART.

12:45.990 --> 12:48.322
IT WAS ALL OVER THE TRADES.
YOU DIDN'T SEE IT?

12:48.330 --> 12:50.798
I DON'T KNOW
HOW I MISSED IT.

12:50.800 --> 12:54.395
YOU SHOULD AUDITION
FOR THE PLAY.

12:54.400 --> 12:56.459
OH, YOU CAN AUDITION
USING ANYTHING.

12:56.470 --> 12:58.665
FRANKLY, WE NEED
SOME PRETTY GIRLS.

12:58.670 --> 13:01.036
YEAH, THANKS ANYWAY.
I CAN'T ACT.

13:01.040 --> 13:04.043
OH, ACTING'S OVERRATED.
YOU'VE GOT PRESENCE, SWEETIE.

13:04.050 --> 13:05.938
LISTEN,
WE'LL CATCH UP LATER.

13:05.950 --> 13:07.872
RIGHT NOW
MY COMPANY NEEDS ME.

13:07.880 --> 13:12.954
OH, THE PLAY IS MY MASTER,
AND I AM ITS WHORE.

13:16.320 --> 13:18.686
SOMEONE REQUEST
TURN-ON SERVICE?

13:18.690 --> 13:21.727
I'M PRETTY SURE
IT'S CALLED TURNDOWN SERVICE.

13:21.730 --> 13:23.698
OH, WELL,
WHO WOULD WANT THAT?

13:23.700 --> 13:25.019
LOGAN'S NOT HERE.

13:25.030 --> 13:26.930
LOOSEN UP,
RICHIE RICH, OKAY?

13:26.940 --> 13:28.760
I'VE BEEN
IN BOTH YOUR BEDS.

13:28.770 --> 13:31.034
I'VE EARNED
THE OCCASIONAL DROP-BY.

13:31.040 --> 13:33.235
[ BABY CRYING ]

13:33.240 --> 13:37.449
OH, MY GOD,
TELL ME THAT IS NOT A BABY.

13:39.010 --> 13:41.012
DON'T BE SILLY.

13:42.250 --> 13:47.051
IT'S AN ANIMATRONIC
PARENTAL-LIFESTYLE SIMULATOR.

13:48.090 --> 13:49.819
IT'S A CLASS PROJECT.

13:50.690 --> 13:53.454
WELL, ISN'T THAT JUST
THE CREEPIEST LITTLE THING

13:53.460 --> 13:54.529
I'VE EVER SEEN?

13:54.530 --> 13:58.694
SO, YOU WANT A BREAK
FROM DADDY DUTY?

13:58.700 --> 14:01.567
LET ME TAKE YOU
FOR A RIDE.

14:01.570 --> 14:02.935
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:02.940 --> 14:04.168
A RIDE?

14:04.170 --> 14:06.035
BIG D's MASERATI
IS DOWNSTAIRS.

14:06.040 --> 14:09.373
YOU GOT TO CHECK IT OUT.
YOU WOULD LOOK SO HOT IN IT.

14:09.380 --> 14:11.871
CAN'T I JUST BE LOVED
FOR ME?

14:11.880 --> 14:14.940
THE MASERATI
RETAILS FOR 150 GRAND,

14:14.950 --> 14:18.249
BUT I'LL LET YOU HAVE HER
FOR HALF THAT.

14:18.250 --> 14:20.810
YOU DO KNOW HOW TO DRIVE
A STICK, DON'T YOU?

14:20.820 --> 14:22.082
ACTUALLY --

14:22.090 --> 14:24.957
DON'T WORRY.
I'LL TEACH YOU THE FUN WAY.

14:24.960 --> 14:28.350
WE DON'T EVEN
HAVE TO LEAVE THE COUCH.

14:33.900 --> 14:36.494
DO THEY, LIKE,
CH EMICALLY CASTRATE YOU BOYS

14:36.500 --> 14:37.865
OVER AT THAT SCHOOL?

14:37.870 --> 14:40.509
YOU DON'T NEED SEX ED.

14:40.510 --> 14:42.831
I AM SEX ED.

14:42.840 --> 14:44.239
[ DOOR OPENS ]

14:46.580 --> 14:47.774
HEY, TRINA.

14:47.780 --> 14:49.873
DUNCAN,
YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD.

14:49.880 --> 14:51.381
IT'S ALL
THE CLEAN LIVING.

14:51.390 --> 14:53.278
HI, BABY.

14:53.290 --> 14:55.417
WHAT TOOK YOU
SO LONG?

14:55.420 --> 14:56.751
HMM.

14:56.760 --> 14:59.149
IF I HAD KNOWN YOU WERE THROWING
YOURSELF AT MY ROOMMATE,

14:59.160 --> 15:00.718
I'D HAVE RACED HOME.

15:00.730 --> 15:02.425
I BROUGHT A SURPRISE
FOR YOU.

15:02.430 --> 15:04.421
I FIGURED YOU AND DUNCAN
COULD TRY IT.

15:04.430 --> 15:06.022
MAYBE IF YOU BOYS
PLAY NICE,

15:06.030 --> 15:09.534
YOU COULD SHARE OR TAKE TURNS
OR SOMETHING.

15:09.540 --> 15:10.768
[ BABY COOS ]

15:10.770 --> 15:12.260
DUNCAN'S NOT INTO
THAT SORT OF THING, PUMPKIN.

15:12.270 --> 15:14.431
I'M TALKING ABOUT
DICK'S MASERATI.

15:14.440 --> 15:15.668
WAIT A MINUTE.

15:15.680 --> 15:19.241
ARE YOU, LIKE,
SLEEPING WITH MY LITTLE BROTHER?

15:19.250 --> 15:20.911
WHAT IS HE -- 13?

15:20.920 --> 15:22.842
13? [ CHUCKLES ]
HE WISHES.

15:22.850 --> 15:27.082
SO, IS THIS YOUR MUCH-OLDER
SISTER I'VE HEARD NOTHING ABOUT?

15:27.090 --> 15:29.058
Logan: AH, YES,
WHERE ARE MY MANNERS?

15:31.930 --> 15:34.194
RODE HARD,
MEET PUT AWAY WET.

15:34.200 --> 15:35.758
I'M GUESSING
SHE'S THE WET ONE.

15:35.760 --> 15:39.526
WELL, I'D LOVE TO STAY AND CHAT,
BUT I'VE GOT PLACES TO BE.

15:39.530 --> 15:40.997
WHERE?

15:41.000 --> 15:42.968
IS THERE A CLUB WHERE YOU,
DEDEE PFEIFFER, JOEY TRAVOLTA,

15:42.970 --> 15:44.608
AND MELISSA RIVERS
ALL MEET FOR DRINKS?

15:44.610 --> 15:46.669
THERE IS.
I DON'T THINK YOU'D LIKE IT.

15:46.670 --> 15:48.206
IT'S 21 AND OVER.

15:48.210 --> 15:50.678
WE'RE HITTING AN AFTER-PARTY
AT CHUCK E. CHEESE, THOUGH,

15:50.680 --> 15:52.204
IF YOU'RE FREE.

15:52.210 --> 15:55.441
OKAY, WELL, I NEED HIM IN BED
BY 10:00 PM. SHARP.

15:55.450 --> 15:57.509
HE'S GOT SCHOOL
TOMORROW.

15:59.120 --> 16:01.054
NIGHT, ALL.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.182
WELL, THE JOKE'S
ON HER.

16:03.190 --> 16:05.226
SHE CAME OVER
TO BORROW MY VIDEO CAMERA.

16:05.230 --> 16:07.596
THE GIRL DOES LOVE
A GOOD EXIT LINE.

16:08.300 --> 16:10.598
AFTER SCOURING
MOM'S SENIOR YEARBOOK,

16:10.600 --> 16:12.591
I FOUND
ONE MYSTERIOUS INSCRIPTION

16:12.600 --> 16:15.967
AMIDST ALL THE "STAY COOL"S
AND "LET'S PARTY THIS SUMMER"S.

16:15.970 --> 16:17.369
ONE PATTY WILSON WROTE,

16:17.370 --> 16:19.838
"LIANNE, THANKS
FOR ALL THE DISHY DISH.

16:19.840 --> 16:21.637
YOU MADE PHYSICS BEARABLE."

16:21.640 --> 16:24.404
LUCKY FOR ME, NOT ONLY DOES
PATTY STILL LIVE IN NEPTUNE,

16:24.410 --> 16:27.413
BUT SHE JUMPED AT THE CHANCE
TO MEET ME FOR COFFEE.

16:27.420 --> 16:30.446
AT LEAST SOMEONE
REMEMBERS MOM FONDLY.

16:30.450 --> 16:31.747
PATTY?

16:31.750 --> 16:35.516
YOU MUST BE VERONICA.
JUST LOOK AT YOU.

16:35.520 --> 16:37.829
PRETTY,
JUST LIKE YOUR MOM.

16:38.690 --> 16:42.854
I'M SURE YOU'LL BE HAPPY TO HEAR
THAT YOUR MOM WAS VERY POPULAR.

16:42.860 --> 16:44.225
THAT'S GREAT.

16:44.230 --> 16:45.595
WE WERE LAB PARTNERS,

16:45.600 --> 16:47.659
AND WE'D JUST SIT
IN THE BACK OF THE ROOM

16:47.670 --> 16:49.638
AND GOSSIP AND SNIPE --
GIRL STUFF.

16:49.640 --> 16:51.130
BUT THE JUICIEST BITS

16:51.140 --> 16:53.734
WERE ALWAYS ABOUT
YOUR MOM'S LOVE LIFE.

16:53.740 --> 16:55.230
REALLY?
WHAT ABOUT?

16:55.240 --> 16:57.902
YOUR MOM AND JAKE KANE --
THE JAKE KANE --

16:57.910 --> 17:00.913
WERE ON AGAIN, OFF AGAIN
THE SUMMER BEFORE SENIOR YEAR.

17:00.920 --> 17:04.583
BUT BY HOMECOMING,
THEY WERE TOGETHER FOR GOOD...

17:04.590 --> 17:05.841
OR SO LIANNE THOUGHT.

17:05.850 --> 17:07.386
WHAT HAPPENED?

17:07.390 --> 17:09.984
THAT SPITEFUL LITTLE SHREW
THAT HE DATED OVER THE SUMMER

17:09.990 --> 17:11.787
TOLD HIM
THAT SHE WAS PREGNANT.

17:11.790 --> 17:15.157
JAKE KANE GOT SOMEBODY PREGNANT
25 YEARS AGO?

17:15.160 --> 17:16.650
WELL, YOUR MOM
DIDN'T THINK SO.

17:16.660 --> 17:18.628
SHE WAS SURE
THAT CELESTE WAS LYING.

17:18.630 --> 17:19.619
CELESTE KANE?

17:19.630 --> 17:21.791
CELESTE CARNATHAN
BACK THEN.

17:21.800 --> 17:24.735
HER FAMILY WAS MOVING
OUT OF THE SCHOOL DISTRICT,

17:24.740 --> 17:26.037
SO SHE HAD TO FIND A WAY

17:26.040 --> 17:27.974
TO BREAK JAKE AND LIANNE UP
FOR GOOD.

17:27.980 --> 17:29.902
CELESTE FINISHED THE YEAR
AT PENN.

17:29.910 --> 17:33.539
OF COURSE, SHE MANAGED
TO FIND HER WAY BACK TO NEPTUNE

17:33.550 --> 17:34.915
FOR PROM.

17:34.920 --> 17:36.842
AND I'M GUESSING SHE WASN'T
PREGNANT AT THE DANCE.

17:36.850 --> 17:41.458
THAT'S RIGHT. JAKE'S LOVE CHILD
HAD MAGICALLY DISAPPEARED.

17:41.460 --> 17:43.121
UH-HUH.

17:43.130 --> 17:46.122
EITHER MOM GOT DUMPED BECAUSE
CELESTE SAID SHE WAS PREGNANT

17:46.130 --> 17:48.121
OR MOM
SAID CELESTE WAS PREGNANT

17:48.130 --> 17:50.098
BECAUSE SHE WAS DUMPED.

17:58.670 --> 18:01.332
SORRY I'M LATE.
Keith: ALMOST STARTED
WITHOUT YOU.

18:01.340 --> 18:03.808
YOU'D HAVE MISSED OUT
ON MY CHILI SURPRISE.

18:03.810 --> 18:05.004
YOU MADE CHILI?

18:05.010 --> 18:06.409
SURPRISE.

18:06.410 --> 18:09.675
HAD TO STOP BY DUNCAN'S
AND PICK UP MY PROGENY.

18:09.680 --> 18:12.240
[ BABY CRYING ]

18:12.250 --> 18:15.151
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION
ABOUT MOM?

18:15.160 --> 18:16.787
SHOOT.

18:16.790 --> 18:21.250
WHEN YOU MET HER, SHE WAS STILL
A COOL PERSON, RIGHT?

18:21.260 --> 18:23.296
OF COURSE SHE WAS COOL.

18:23.300 --> 18:25.825
SHE MARRIED ME,
DIDN'T SHE?

18:27.100 --> 18:28.761
WHY DO YOU ASK?

18:28.770 --> 18:32.137
I JUST FOUND OUT THAT MOM
WAS SUSPENDED HER SENIOR YEAR.

18:32.140 --> 18:33.869
I'M PRETTY SURE

18:33.880 --> 18:36.371
IT WAS FOR SPREADING A RUMOR
THAT CELESTE KANE WAS PREGNANT.

18:36.380 --> 18:38.200
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
VERY COOL.

18:38.210 --> 18:40.314
MY POINT EXACTLY.

18:40.320 --> 18:43.039
DO ME A FAVOR?
WHAT KIND OF FAVOR?

18:43.050 --> 18:44.415
ACCESS THE COUNTY
BIRTH RECORDS,

18:44.420 --> 18:46.183
FIND OUT IF MOM
WAS TELLING THE TRUTH.

18:46.190 --> 18:48.750
AND THAT'S GONNA
TELL YOU WHAT?

18:49.590 --> 18:51.558
YOU KNOW
WHO YOUR MOM WAS.

18:51.560 --> 18:54.028
FORGET THE PAST
COUPLE OF YEARS.

18:54.030 --> 18:56.828
YOU LOVED HER.
SHE LOVED YOU.

19:03.610 --> 19:06.704
WHICH IS MORE TORTUROUS --
ORGANIZING DISCIPLINARY FILES

19:06.710 --> 19:08.769
OR SPENDING LUNCH
WATCHING THE BARD

19:08.780 --> 19:12.079
GET FLOGGED BY THE SECOND LEAD
OF "WILDER THINGS."

19:12.080 --> 19:13.149
HA HA!

19:13.150 --> 19:15.209
ARE YOU HONEST?

19:15.220 --> 19:16.812
MY LORD?

19:16.820 --> 19:18.048
ARE YOU FAIR?

19:18.050 --> 19:20.086
WHAT MEANS
YOUR LORDSHIP?

19:20.090 --> 19:22.217
[ BABY CRYING ]

19:22.960 --> 19:26.589
OOPS, SORRY. IT'S MINE.
HE'S JUST A LITTLE COLICKY.

19:26.590 --> 19:29.696
THAT IF YOU BE HONEST
AND FAIR,

19:29.700 --> 19:33.488
YOUR HONESTY SHOULD ADMIT
NO DISCOURSE TO YOUR BEAUTY.

19:33.500 --> 19:37.209
COULD BEAUTY, MY LORD, HAVE
BETTER COMMERCE THAN WITH...

19:37.910 --> 19:39.207
AAH!

19:39.210 --> 19:41.633
GO GET THE NURSE.

19:53.990 --> 19:55.480
YOU ARE TOO CUTE.

19:55.490 --> 19:58.823
YOU WANT
TO HAVE A MEETING.

19:58.830 --> 20:00.081
I LOVE IT!

20:00.090 --> 20:04.197
SO, WHAT'S THIS
ALL ABOUT?

20:05.270 --> 20:06.897
WHAT'S THAT?

20:06.900 --> 20:10.131
THIS IS THE BOX FOR MY FATHER'S
$15,000 PANERAI DESTRO

20:10.140 --> 20:13.200
THAT YOU SOLD TO THE WEBBERS
FOR 5 GRAND.

20:14.680 --> 20:18.138
THIS FAMILY HAS BEEN
HUMILIATED ENOUGH ALREADY.

20:18.150 --> 20:19.606
YOU NEED TO STOP.

20:19.610 --> 20:21.214
YEAH.

20:21.220 --> 20:23.688
HE BILKS INVESTORS FOR MILLIONS,
BUT I'M HUMILIATING THE FAMILY?

20:23.690 --> 20:26.488
I DON'T HAVE A LITTLE TRUST FUND
TO TAKE CARE OF ME,

20:26.490 --> 20:29.584
SO A GIRL'S GOT TO DO
WHAT A GIRL'S GOT TO DO.

20:29.590 --> 20:32.855
I HAVE
A BETTER SOLUTION.

20:32.860 --> 20:34.191
HMM?

20:34.200 --> 20:36.555
I'M USING MY TRUST FUND
TO START A REAL-ESTATE BUSINESS.

20:36.560 --> 20:39.165
I'VE ALREADY FOUND
SOME OFFICE SPACE DOWNTOWN,

20:39.170 --> 20:40.592
AND I'VE DRAWN UP
A PROSPECTUS,

20:40.600 --> 20:42.591
IF YOU'D LIKE
TO TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

20:42.600 --> 20:44.500
WHAT'S THIS
GOT TO DO WITH ME?

20:44.510 --> 20:46.603
I'M 16 --
I CAN'T MEET WITH INVESTORS.

20:46.610 --> 20:48.475
I CAN'T SIGN
LEGAL DOCUMENTS.

20:48.480 --> 20:50.573
NOW, THIS IS WHERE YOU
WOULD COME IN.

20:50.580 --> 20:53.378
YOU WOULD BE THE FACE
OF THE PHOENIX LAND TRUST.

20:53.380 --> 20:56.713
GEE, CASSIDY,
I DIDN'T THINK YOU LIKED ME.

20:56.720 --> 21:01.783
I DON'T, BUT I FIND VALUE
IN YOUR DESPERATION.

21:07.430 --> 21:11.321
LOOK, KID, I HAVE WORKED
VERY HARD OVER THE YEARS

21:11.330 --> 21:12.592
TO AVOID WORKING.

21:12.600 --> 21:15.194
NOW YOU WANT
TO GIVE ME A JOB?

21:15.200 --> 21:16.462
I KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT SALES.

21:16.470 --> 21:18.529
SURE YOU DO.
THAT'S ALL YOU KNOW.

21:18.540 --> 21:20.679
LOOK, YOU'LL BE SALARIED --
A GRAND A WEEK

21:20.680 --> 21:23.103
PLUS COMMISSION THAT
YOU'LL SEE OUTLINED THERE.

21:23.110 --> 21:25.601
BIG "D" IS GONNA
GET THROUGH THIS EVENTUALLY.

21:25.610 --> 21:27.771
IT'S SWEET
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO.

21:27.780 --> 21:30.385
YOUR DAD
WOULD BE SO PROUD.

21:31.750 --> 21:34.856
IF YOU WANT THIS LITTLE
ARRANGEMENT TO WORK,

21:34.860 --> 21:36.885
TRY NOT
TO PATRONIZE ME.

21:36.890 --> 21:38.778
SIR.

21:38.790 --> 21:41.020
YES, SIR.

21:41.030 --> 21:43.919
SO, WHEN DO I GET
MY FIRST CHECK?

21:52.440 --> 21:54.533
THERE'S NO BABY
BORN IN 1980

21:54.540 --> 21:57.907
UNDER EITHER LAST NAME,
KANE OR CARNATHAN.

21:57.910 --> 21:59.502
SO CELESTE WAS LYING.

21:59.510 --> 22:02.718
THAT OR SHE MIGHT'VE
HAD AN ABORTION.

22:02.720 --> 22:05.382
IS THAT THE TYPE OF THING
YOU CAN CHECK UP ON?

22:05.390 --> 22:08.314
HONEY, IT LOOKS TO ME
LIKE YOU AND DUNCAN

22:08.320 --> 22:10.527
HAVE A NICE LITTLE THING
GOING,

22:10.530 --> 22:12.680
SO WHY DO YOU
HAVE TO GO OUT OF YOUR WAY

22:12.690 --> 22:14.624
TO PICK OFF
A 25-YEAR-OLD SCAB?

22:14.630 --> 22:17.861
I JUST WANT A LITTLE PROOF
THAT MY MOM WAS A GOOD PERSON,

22:17.870 --> 22:21.169
THAT SHE WASN'T ONE OF THE GIRLS
I HATE SO MUCH,

22:21.170 --> 22:22.660
ONE OF THE GIRLS

22:22.670 --> 22:25.400
THAT MAKES HIGH SCHOOL MISERABLE
FOR EVERYONE ELSE.

22:25.410 --> 22:28.038
OKAY.

22:28.040 --> 22:29.200
WHAT?

22:29.210 --> 22:30.871
KIND OF A BONUS,
ISN'T IT,

22:30.880 --> 22:33.303
THAT YOU CAN PROVE CELESTE
IS THE WITCH YOU THINK SHE IS

22:33.310 --> 22:34.675
AT THE SAME TIME?

22:34.680 --> 22:38.309
IF SHE DIDN'T SPLIT
JAKE AND YOUR MOM UP,

22:38.320 --> 22:39.810
WELL,
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE ME.

22:39.820 --> 22:42.584
AND THAT MEANS
YOU WOULDN'T BE YOU, VERONICA.

22:42.590 --> 22:46.959
AND THAT
WOULD BE BAD, RIGHT?

22:46.960 --> 22:48.291
RIGHT.

22:48.300 --> 22:52.464
SO, TRY TO KEEP THAT IN MIND
WHEN I TELL YOU THIS.

22:54.000 --> 22:58.266
A JANE DOE BABY WAS DELIVERED
TO THE BALBOA COUNTY HOSPITAL

22:58.270 --> 23:00.158
ON MAY 8, 1980.

23:00.170 --> 23:02.070
THAT'S WEIRD.

23:02.080 --> 23:03.445
IT GETS WEIRDER.

23:03.450 --> 23:05.577
THEY FOUND THE BABY
IN THE GIRLS' BATHROOM

23:05.580 --> 23:07.946
DURING THE NEPTUNE
HIGH SCHOOL PROM.

23:07.950 --> 23:09.247
CELESTE.

23:09.250 --> 23:11.582
YOU DON'T ACTUALLY LISTEN
WHEN I TALK, DO YOU?

23:14.190 --> 23:16.886
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

23:19.190 --> 23:20.657
YOU'RE IT.

23:20.660 --> 23:23.128
OH, NO, NO, NO.
JUNIOR'S ALL YOURS TONIGHT.

23:23.130 --> 23:26.122
BABY AND CHEESEBURGERS.
IT'S A PACKAGE DEAL.

23:26.130 --> 23:29.497
I HAVE TO GET SOME SLEEP
TONIGHT -- CIVICS TEST.

23:29.500 --> 23:31.604
I WOULD IF I COULD,
BUT I'VE GOT PLANS.

23:31.610 --> 23:35.000
PLANS? I DON'T REMEMBER YOU
RUNNING ANYTHING BY ME.

23:35.010 --> 23:36.875
[ BABY CRIES ]

23:36.880 --> 23:38.939
UGH.

23:38.950 --> 23:40.975
I LEFT THE BOTTLE
IN MY CAR.

23:43.150 --> 23:45.812
WELL, AT LEAST YOU BROUGHT
THE BABY UP THIS TIME.

23:45.820 --> 23:49.415
LOOK, I'LL HANDLE THIS, BUT THEN
YOU'VE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

23:49.420 --> 23:51.229
DO YOU HAVE A CHICK
COMING OVER?

23:51.230 --> 23:53.596
I'M GOING OUT TO DINNER.

23:55.430 --> 23:58.069
I'M SURPRISED THAT MOM NEVER GOT
ONE OF THESE THINGS FOR LILLY.

23:58.070 --> 24:01.096
SHE WAS ALWAYS SO TERRIFIED
THAT LILLY WOULD GET PREGNANT.

24:01.100 --> 24:02.397
THAT'S IRONIC.

24:02.400 --> 24:03.833
WHAT'S IRONIC?

24:03.840 --> 24:06.661
YOUR MOM AFRAID THAT LILLY
WOULD GET PREGNANT.

24:06.670 --> 24:09.969
HEY, NOW, YOU'RE NOT ABOUT TO
BAD-MOUTH CELESTE, ARE YOU?

24:09.980 --> 24:11.174
HEAVENS NO.

24:11.180 --> 24:15.241
I MEAN, WHAT COULD I SAY
ABOUT THAT...SAINT?

24:15.250 --> 24:19.846
SHE IS A WARMHEARTED,
GOOD-HUMORED, LOVELY WOMAN

24:19.850 --> 24:23.752
OF HIGH BREEDING
AND IMPECCABLE SOCIAL GRACE.

24:23.760 --> 24:26.957
WHY, THANK YOU,
VERONICA.

24:32.900 --> 24:33.594
MOM.

24:33.600 --> 24:35.158
HEY, YOU'RE EARLY.

24:35.170 --> 24:37.764
I WANTED TO GIVE YOU YOUR
CLEAN CLOTHES BEFORE DINNER.

24:37.770 --> 24:39.408
WHAT IS SHE
DOING HERE?

24:39.410 --> 24:41.173
"SHE" MEANING ME?

24:41.180 --> 24:45.446
I GUESS I'M HERE
AS DUNCAN'S SECRET GIRLFRIEND.

24:45.450 --> 24:48.044
OH, AND WE HAVE
A LOVE CHILD.

24:48.050 --> 24:49.517
[ BABY COOS ]

24:49.520 --> 24:51.044
WANT TO HOLD HER?

24:51.050 --> 24:52.449
SHE'S SNUGGLY.

24:52.450 --> 24:53.815
I'LL PASS.

24:53.820 --> 24:57.119
ASTRID, IF YOU'RE DONE GAPING,
THE CLOTHES?

24:57.120 --> 24:59.850
I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD'VE TOLD THEM.

24:59.860 --> 25:02.328
OR MENTIONED TO ME
THAT YOU HADN'T.

25:02.330 --> 25:04.491
I TOLD YOUR FATHER SOMETHING
LIKE THIS WOULD HAPPEN.

25:04.500 --> 25:07.424
THIS IS EXACTLY WHY WE
SHOULD'VE TAKEN YOU UP TO NAPA.

25:07.430 --> 25:09.136
[ GASPS ]
NOT IN FRONT OF THE BABY.

25:09.140 --> 25:11.062
THIS ISN'T AMUSING,
VERONICA.

25:11.070 --> 25:14.278
IT'S NOT.
ME BREEDING WITH A KANE?

25:14.280 --> 25:15.633
NO LAUGHING MATTER.

25:15.640 --> 25:17.505
BUT, LOOK, NO ONE
HAS TO KNOW, RIGHT?

25:17.510 --> 25:20.274
WORST CASE SCENARIO,
THINGS DON'T WORK OUT,

25:20.280 --> 25:22.919
I'LL JUST DUMP HER OFF
AT THE BIG DANCE.

25:22.920 --> 25:25.013
IT WORKED AT YOUR PROM,
DIDN'T IT?

25:25.020 --> 25:27.443
DOES SHE EVER MAKE SENSE,
DUNCAN?

25:27.450 --> 25:29.418
DOES SHE EVER THAW OUT,
DUNCAN?

25:29.420 --> 25:31.251
WHEN I LOOK
AT YOUR FACE,

25:31.260 --> 25:34.252
ALL I SEE IS YOUR DRUNK
SLUT OF A MOTHER.

25:34.260 --> 25:36.148
MA!
LOOK, DUNCAN,
SHE CAN'T JUST --

25:36.160 --> 25:38.424
VERONICA, I NEED A MOMENT ALONE
WITH MY MOM.

25:38.430 --> 25:40.091
SURE.
WE'LL BE IN THE BEDROOM.

25:40.100 --> 25:42.034
YOU DON'T MIND
YOUR DIRTY LAUNDRY

25:42.040 --> 25:44.759
MIXING WITH YOUR CLEAN LAUNDRY,
DO YOU?

25:47.940 --> 25:50.579
NICE BOSS
YOU GOT OUT THERE.

25:50.580 --> 25:51.774
OOH, YEAH.

25:51.780 --> 25:53.441
HOW CAN YOU
PUT UP WITH HER?

25:53.450 --> 25:56.613
SHE PROMISED TO PAY MY WAY
THROUGH GRAD SCHOOL NEXT YEAR.

25:56.620 --> 25:58.645
KIND OF A WEIRD QUESTION,

25:58.650 --> 26:01.915
BUT IS THAT YOUR REAL
HAIR COLOR, ASTRID?

26:01.920 --> 26:04.320
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THAT IS A WEIRD QUESTION.

26:04.330 --> 26:07.481
I'M MORE OF WHAT YOU'D CALL
A BOTTLE BLONDE.

26:07.490 --> 26:09.856
AND I'M GUESSING
YOU'RE ABOUT 25?

26:09.860 --> 26:12.863
YOU SHOULD REALLY
WORK AT A CARNIVAL.

26:12.870 --> 26:14.030
I AM INDEED 25.

26:14.040 --> 26:17.259
PLEASE, DON'T ASK ME
MY WEIGHT.

26:17.270 --> 26:20.535
WE'RE LEAVING --
NOW.

26:20.540 --> 26:22.576
[ SIGHS ]

26:25.810 --> 26:28.313
SO, IS THAT HOW CELESTE
LIVES WITH HERSELF?

26:28.320 --> 26:31.187
SHE HIRES HER ABANDONED
DAUGHTER TO FOLD LAUNDRY

26:31.190 --> 26:33.442
IN EXCHANGE
FOR PAYING HER TUITION?

26:33.450 --> 26:35.213
IF ASTRID IS THE PROM BABY,

26:35.220 --> 26:38.951
SHE'S GOT A WHOLE HELL OF A LOT
MORE COMING HER WAY.

26:38.960 --> 26:40.791
EXCUSE ME,
MRS. MURPHY?

26:40.800 --> 26:42.153
YES, LOGAN?

26:42.160 --> 26:44.196
HEY, YOU MIND IF I TAKE
A BATHROOM BREAK?

26:44.200 --> 26:47.897
YOU ALWAYS ASK TO GO TO THE
BATHROOM DURING THIS PERIOD.

26:47.900 --> 26:51.108
I KNOW. IT'S THAT 12-PACK
I SLAM AT LUNCH.

26:51.110 --> 26:53.567
IT GOES
RIGHT THROUGH ME.

26:53.570 --> 26:55.629
HURRY BACK, LOGAN.

27:02.780 --> 27:06.113
Logan:
I HOPE THAT TAPE DIDN'T BURN TOO
MUCH WHEN THEY RIPPED IT OFF.

27:06.120 --> 27:08.111
I HEAR THAT
CAN LEAVE SOME CHAFING.

27:08.120 --> 27:09.712
YOU MADE
THE WRONG PLAY, DOG.

27:09.720 --> 27:11.381
I SHOULDN'T LET YOU LIVE
FOR WHAT YOU PULLED.

27:11.390 --> 27:14.826
WHAT I PULLED?
HANG ON, COMPADRE, LET'S RECAP.

27:14.830 --> 27:18.789
YOU BLASTED A SHOTGUN
THROUGH MY CAR WITH ME INSIDE.

27:18.800 --> 27:20.199
THAT WASN'T ME.

27:20.200 --> 27:21.838
YOU TORCHED MY HOUSE.

27:21.840 --> 27:23.239
THEN YOUR MASKED BANDIDOS

27:23.240 --> 27:25.834
PLAYED RUSSIAN ROULETTE
WITH MY HAND, OKAY?

27:25.840 --> 27:27.774
MY MATH SAYS
YOU STILL OWE ME.

27:27.780 --> 27:29.475
I THOUGHT
YOU KILLED FELIX.

27:29.480 --> 27:30.777
I DIDN'T.

27:30.780 --> 27:33.101
YEAH, I PRETTY MUCH
KNOW THAT NOW.

27:33.110 --> 27:35.010
ARE YOU WAITING
FOR THE MUSIC TO SWELL

27:35.020 --> 27:36.578
BEFORE YOU START
THE APOLOGY?

27:36.580 --> 27:38.719
WE HAVE SOMETHING
IN COMMON NOW.

27:38.720 --> 27:41.314
WE BOTH NEED TO FIND OUT
WHO KILLED FELIX.

27:41.320 --> 27:44.187
SO, WHAT, WE TEAM UP,
GET MATCHING CAPES,

27:44.190 --> 27:46.226
I RIDE SHOTGUN
IN A SIDECAR?

27:46.230 --> 27:48.118
SOMETHING LIKE THAT,
BUT NOT YET.

27:48.130 --> 27:49.722
SEE, I CAN'T
LET YOU LEAVE HERE

27:49.730 --> 27:51.493
LOOKING THE WAY YOU DID
WHEN YOU WALKED IN,

27:51.500 --> 27:53.968
NOT IF I DON'T WANT TO END UP
SOME BALD GUY WITH TATTOOS

27:53.970 --> 27:55.528
WHO RIDES
THE SCHOOL BUS.

27:55.540 --> 27:58.862
I HOPE YOU DON'T JUST EXPECT ME
TO STAND HERE AND TAKE IT.

27:58.870 --> 28:00.406
WOULDN'T BE MUCH FUN
IF YOU DID.

28:00.410 --> 28:02.105
WHO'S GONNA THROW
THE FIRST --
[ BELL RINGS ]

28:02.110 --> 28:04.408
[ THE HIVES' "WALK, IDIOT, WALK"
PLAYS ]

28:07.250 --> 28:09.844
*OW!*

28:21.060 --> 28:24.359
* WELL, IS IT TRUE
WHAT THEY SAY ABOUT IT? *

28:24.370 --> 28:26.861
* THEY SAY IT'S NEW,
BUT I HAVE TO DOUBT IT *

28:26.870 --> 28:29.361
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
MOVE IT.

28:29.370 --> 28:31.031
COME ON, GET TO CLASS.

28:31.040 --> 28:34.168
* HAD ENOUGH *

28:34.180 --> 28:38.173
* I GOT SOME PEOPLE
SAYING THIS WAY *

28:38.180 --> 28:41.513
* I GOT SOME PEOPLE
SAYING THAT WAY *

28:41.520 --> 28:44.512
GET OFF!

28:44.520 --> 28:47.546
* AIN'T IT TOUGH? *

28:47.550 --> 28:50.348
* SEE THE IDIOT WALK *

28:50.360 --> 28:52.624
OKAY, LET'S GO, FOLKS,
LET'S GO.

28:52.630 --> 28:53.654
NOTHING TO SEE HERE.

28:53.660 --> 28:55.059
COME ON, LET'S GO.

28:55.060 --> 28:57.927
* SEE THE IDIOT
CHALK UP HIS NAME *

28:57.930 --> 28:59.761
THEY'RE LUCKY
THEY GOT THAT DOOR DOWN.

28:59.770 --> 29:01.135
SOUNDED LIKE WEEVIL

29:01.140 --> 29:03.233
WAS JUST BEATING THE FRECKLES
OFF HIS ASS.

29:04.110 --> 29:05.532
DID YOU SEE HIM
WALK BY?

29:05.540 --> 29:08.202
WASN'T MUCH LEFT
OFF THAT PRETTY 09er FACE.

29:08.210 --> 29:10.098
BUT HE WALKED,
DIDN'T HE?

29:10.110 --> 29:13.079
IF THAT WAS ME,
AFTER WHAT SURFER BOY DID,

29:13.080 --> 29:15.913
I WOULD'VE PUT HIM
IN THE GROUND.

29:20.220 --> 29:22.051
I GAVE YOU
A FEW OPTIONS.

29:22.060 --> 29:25.689
HERE'S IF YOU WANT TO GO WITH
THE WHOLE FLASH ANIMATION ROUTE.

29:25.690 --> 29:28.124
SWEET.

29:28.130 --> 29:31.395
BUT IF YOU'RE WORRIED ABOUT
INDUCING EPILEPTIC FITS

29:31.400 --> 29:32.594
WITH YOUR CLIENTS,

29:32.600 --> 29:36.934
WE CAN GO WITH A MORE SLEEK
GRAPHIC VERSION.

29:36.940 --> 29:38.760
I LIKE SLEEK.

29:38.770 --> 29:40.237
ME TOO.

29:42.110 --> 29:46.274
"PHOENIX LAND TRUST, INC.
CASSIDY CASABLANCAS, CEO."

29:46.280 --> 29:47.645
NICE!

29:47.650 --> 29:49.743
I WOULD TOTALLY TRUST
THIS COMPANY WITH MY MONEY.

29:49.750 --> 29:52.014
AND IT'LL WORK WONDERS
WITH THE LADIES.

29:52.020 --> 29:54.853
CHICKS DIG SCARS
AND ACRONYMS.

29:54.860 --> 29:56.054
GOOD TO KNOW.

29:56.060 --> 29:57.687
I'M A GIVER OF INFO.

29:57.690 --> 30:00.727
YEAH, WELL, AS MUCH AS I'D LIKE
TO IMPRESS THE LADIES

30:00.730 --> 30:02.459
WITH MY TITLE,

30:02.460 --> 30:06.396
I ACTUALLY NEED THE CEO TO BE
LISTED AS KENDALL CASABLANCAS.

30:06.400 --> 30:08.539
PAY ME IN CASH,
I ASK NO QUESTIONS.

30:08.540 --> 30:12.328
JUST TIP ME OFF
WHEN YOU'RE GOING PUBLIC.

30:12.340 --> 30:16.276
YOU KNOW, I THINK
THAT MIGHT BE ILLEGAL.

30:16.280 --> 30:17.508
STILL.

30:17.510 --> 30:20.399
YOU'RE ADMIRING MY MOXIE,
AREN'T YOU.

30:22.080 --> 30:24.389
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

30:28.220 --> 30:31.257
YOU MUST BE MRS. MAHNOVSKI.
THANKS FOR COMING DOWN.

30:31.260 --> 30:34.388
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND
FOLLOWING ME INTO MY OFFICE.

30:36.030 --> 30:37.725
ADOPTION AGENCIES

30:39.500 --> 30:41.468
TEMPORARY FOSTER PARENTS,
HOWEVER,

30:47.110 --> 30:48.668
I SEE YOU
AND YOUR HUSBAND

30:48.680 --> 30:51.274
HAVE TAKEN IN A NUMBER
OF CHILDREN OVER THE YEARS.

30:51.280 --> 30:54.340
YOU DON'T HAPPEN TO REMEMBER
A LITTLE GIRL

30:54.350 --> 30:57.217
WHO WAS IN YOUR CARE
FOR A FEW WEEKS BACK IN 1980?

30:57.220 --> 30:58.915
SHE WAS THE ONE
WHO WAS...

30:58.920 --> 31:00.285
FOUND
IN THE HIGH SCHOOL.

31:00.290 --> 31:02.212
HOW COULD I FORGET
THE PROM BABY?

31:02.220 --> 31:03.983
THE PROM BABY, RIGHT.

31:03.990 --> 31:06.288
WELL, MY CLIENTS
SEEM TO THINK

31:06.290 --> 31:09.396
SHE MIGHT BE THEIR
VERY OWN LONG-LOST CHILD.

31:09.400 --> 31:10.549
WELL, I'LL BE.

31:10.560 --> 31:12.790
MY CLIENTS DON'T WANT
A LOT OF PUBLICITY.

31:12.800 --> 31:16.292
THEY'RE QUITE WEALTHY, AND
THEY'RE REALLY ONLY INTERESTED

31:16.300 --> 31:18.564
IN TAKING CARE OF THE CHILD
FINANCIALLY.

31:18.570 --> 31:20.765
SO, IF YOU COULD JUST POINT ME
IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION...

31:20.770 --> 31:23.705
I'M JUST NOT SURE THEIR MONEY
WOULD MEAN ALL THAT MUCH TO HER.

31:23.710 --> 31:25.348
REALLY?
WHY IS THAT?

31:25.350 --> 31:28.478
I HAPPEN TO KNOW SHE ENDED UP
IN A WEALTHY LOCAL HOME.

31:28.480 --> 31:29.515
SHE DID?

31:29.520 --> 31:31.613
THOUGH THIS PAST YEAR,
I'M AFRAID,

31:31.620 --> 31:34.350
HER ADOPTIVE MOTHER
COMMITTED SUICIDE

31:34.360 --> 31:37.318
AND HER ADOPTIVE FATHER
WENT TO JAIL.

31:46.530 --> 31:48.168
BY ALL RIGHTS,
I SHOULD JUST LET THIS DROP.

31:48.170 --> 31:49.831
I CAN'T PRETEND
I'M RIGHTING A WRONG.

31:49.840 --> 31:51.432
I'M NOT RESCUING A HOUSEKEEPER.

31:51.440 --> 31:53.362
BE HONEST WITH YOURSELF,
VERONICA.

31:53.370 --> 31:55.270
YOU JUST CAN'T STAND
CELESTE KANE,

31:55.280 --> 31:57.430
AND YOU WANT
TO SEE HER HUMILIATED.

31:57.440 --> 31:59.647
HEARD YOU WERE
STILL IN HERE.

31:59.650 --> 32:03.541
YEAH, THEY'RE KEEPING ME
ANOTHER DAY FOR OBSERVATION.

32:03.550 --> 32:05.814
DOC WANTS TO MAKE SURE
THE SWELLING GOES DOWN

32:05.820 --> 32:08.516
BEFORE I LEAVE.

32:08.520 --> 32:09.748
I SHOULD LET YOU REST.

32:09.760 --> 32:11.955
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHY
I'M BOTHERING YOU WITH THIS.

32:11.960 --> 32:13.996
WHAT'S THAT YOU'VE GOT?

32:14.000 --> 32:15.797
NOTHING.

32:15.800 --> 32:18.291
I WAS JUST THINKING
OF TRYING OUT FOR THE PLAY.

32:18.300 --> 32:22.259
AND I WANTED TO TAPE MYSELF,
MAYBE GET SOME DIRECTION.

32:30.610 --> 32:33.272
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

32:33.280 --> 32:36.579
DON'T DO THIS
TO YOURSELF.

32:36.580 --> 32:39.913
YOU'RE DYING.
CAN'T YOU SEE YOU'RE DYING?

32:39.920 --> 32:42.684
THEN PLEASE
LET ME DIE IN PEACE.

32:42.690 --> 32:45.784
I CAN'T DO THAT,
BECAUSE THERE IS HOPE.

32:45.790 --> 32:47.155
THERE'S ALWAYS HOPE.

32:47.160 --> 32:50.254
I DON'T NEED HOPE.
I NEED BONE MARROW.

32:50.260 --> 32:54.435
MY DOCTOR SAID ONLY
A BLOOD RELATION CAN SAVE ME.

32:54.440 --> 32:57.364
WHAT ABOUT YOUR PARENTS?
I'M ADOPTED.

32:57.370 --> 33:01.636
UNLESS THE MOTHER
WHO ABANDONED ME COMES FORWARD,

33:01.640 --> 33:05.303
UNLESS I FIND OUT
WHO I REALLY AM...

33:05.310 --> 33:07.369
IT'S OVER FOR ME.

33:07.380 --> 33:09.018
[ SOBS ]

33:10.520 --> 33:11.748
AND SCENE.

33:12.520 --> 33:14.488
YOU KNOW,
I REALLY AM ADOPTED.

33:14.490 --> 33:17.982
REALLY?
I -- I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

33:21.160 --> 33:22.923
SO, WHO'S THE MEAN GIRL NOW?

33:22.930 --> 33:24.568
TO DO WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE,

33:24.570 --> 33:26.720
I WOULDN'T
JUST BE SHAMING CELESTE.

33:26.730 --> 33:30.166
I'D BE MAKING A PUBLIC
SPECTACLE OUT OF TRINA.

33:32.710 --> 33:35.008
OKAY, TRINA,
I WAS LYING.

33:35.010 --> 33:38.343
THAT WHOLE BIT ABOUT WANTING TO
TRY OUT FOR THE PLAY -- A LIE.

33:38.350 --> 33:41.001
THE TRUTH IS, AS A BABY,

33:41.010 --> 33:44.787
YOU WERE LEFT IN A NEPTUNE HIGH
GIRLS' BATHROOM ON PROM NIGHT

33:44.790 --> 33:46.143
25 YEARS AGO.

33:46.150 --> 33:48.414
NO WAY.

33:48.420 --> 33:51.685
ASHTON KUTCHER
IS HIDING SOMEWHERE, RIGHT?

33:51.690 --> 33:53.885
ASHTON, COME OUT.

33:53.890 --> 33:55.653
YOU CAN'T GET ME
THAT EASY.

33:55.660 --> 33:57.389
TRINA, I'M DEAD SERIOUS.

33:57.400 --> 33:58.560
OKAY.

33:58.570 --> 34:00.697
IF YOU'RE JOKING,
YOU REALLY CAN ACT.

34:00.700 --> 34:02.133
YOU'RE A NATURAL.

34:02.140 --> 34:04.108
YOU WERE FOUND IN A GIRLS'
BATHROOM ON PROM NIGHT.

34:04.110 --> 34:05.759
WHAT?

34:05.770 --> 34:09.103
SO, YOU MEAN MY MOTHER WAS,
LIKE, ONE OF THOSE TRASHY SLUTS

34:09.110 --> 34:11.203
THAT DUMPED ME
IN A GARBAGE CAN?

34:11.210 --> 34:16.273
I'M PRETTY SURE
CELESTE KANE IS YOUR MOM.

34:18.250 --> 34:21.708
WELL, THERE'S WORSE NEWS
YOU COULD'VE GIVEN ME.

34:21.720 --> 34:23.017
THEY'VE GOT BILLIONS.

34:23.020 --> 34:24.578
I SUPPOSE THEY DO.

34:24.590 --> 34:29.857
UM...I WAS GONNA USE THIS
AUDITION TAPE TO SMOKE HER OUT,

34:29.860 --> 34:31.259
SHAME HER.

34:31.270 --> 34:34.262
I WAS GONNA SEND THIS VIDEO
TO ALL THE TABLOIDS.

34:34.270 --> 34:38.058
OH, YOU'RE A RASCAL,
VERONICA MARS.

34:38.070 --> 34:39.537
AM I?

34:39.540 --> 34:42.031
I WAS THINKING I WAS
SOMETHING ELSE LESS FLATTERING.

34:42.040 --> 34:43.576
YOU KNOW, IF WE HURRY,

34:43.580 --> 34:45.343
THAT TAPE CAN MAKE
TONIGHT'S ENTERTAINMENT NEWS.

34:45.350 --> 34:47.944
OH, IT'S THE LEAST BIG PAT
CAN DO FOR ME

34:47.950 --> 34:52.284
AFTER LEAVING ALL THOSE
PERW MESSAGES ON MY VOICE MAIL.

34:54.660 --> 34:55.957
Boy: "POOR YORICK.

34:55.960 --> 34:57.552
I KNEW HIM, HORATIO,
A FELLOW --"

34:57.560 --> 35:00.449
OKAY, PEOPLE,
TAKE FIVE.

35:01.760 --> 35:03.057
OH!

35:03.060 --> 35:05.062
"STARLET'S SILENT STRUGGLE
WITH DEATH."

35:05.070 --> 35:07.265
"THE ECHOLLS
FAMILY CURSE."

35:07.270 --> 35:09.989
"WEBSTER RUMORED
TO BE DISCOVERED

35:10.000 --> 35:12.264
IN NEVERLAND BASEMENT."

35:13.810 --> 35:16.677
I'M SORRY.
YOU HAVE TO GO SLOWER.

35:16.680 --> 35:18.500
LOOK --
IT'S LUNCH LADY DORIS.

35:18.510 --> 35:21.240
DORIS WAS SO NICE TO ME
WHEN I WENT HERE.

35:21.250 --> 35:23.571
USED TO ALWAYS GIVE ME
EXTRA CAKE.

35:23.580 --> 35:25.719
ACTUALLY,
HER NAME IS MARY.

35:25.720 --> 35:28.109
REALLY? GUESS I JUST DECIDED
TO CALL HER DORIS.

35:28.120 --> 35:30.418
YOU WANT TO HELP?
OH, THAT'S SO SWEET.

35:30.420 --> 35:33.787
TELL HER THANKS, BUT THIS
IS A STUDENT PRODUCTION.

35:33.790 --> 35:35.849
TRINA?

35:38.930 --> 35:40.898
WHAT'S SHE SAYING?

35:43.900 --> 35:49.679
VERONICA, COULD YOU PLEASE
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON?

35:51.140 --> 35:55.509
SHE'S SAYING SHE WANTS
TO GIVE YOU HER BONE MARROW.

36:17.400 --> 36:20.301
TRINA IS REALLY
YOUR DAUGHTER?

36:23.410 --> 36:25.344
TRINA WAS THE PROM BABY?

36:29.380 --> 36:32.543
WHAT DID MY MOTHER DO
TO HURT YOU?

36:35.890 --> 36:39.280
"HURT? YOU MOTHER
WAS MY FRIEND."

36:39.290 --> 36:41.121
FRIEND?

36:41.130 --> 36:44.395
LIANNE WAS YOUR FRIEND?

36:44.400 --> 36:47.494
WHAT A DIFFERENCE
A LETTER MAKES.

36:47.500 --> 36:48.865
"LIANNE COULD SIGN.

36:48.870 --> 36:51.532
"SHE'D EAT LUNCH WITH ME
MOST OF THE TIME.

36:51.540 --> 36:54.976
SHE WAS THE SWEETEST,
COOLEST GIRL IN SCHOOL."

37:03.520 --> 37:06.614
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS A KID,
I USED TO IMAGINE

37:06.620 --> 37:10.886
THAT SOMEDAY I'D FIND OUT MY
PARENTS WERE, LIKE, MOVIE STARS.

37:10.890 --> 37:14.326
TRINA, YOUR PARENTS
ACTUALLY WERE MOVIE STARS.

37:14.330 --> 37:16.321
I MEAN
MY REAL PARENTS.

37:16.330 --> 37:20.391
SO, WHY ARE YOU SO INTERESTED
IN ALL THIS?

37:20.400 --> 37:22.789
25 YEARS AGO,
MARY TOLD MY MOTHER

37:22.800 --> 37:26.133
SHE WAS HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH A FACULTY MEMBER,

37:26.140 --> 37:27.562
AND MOM MADE THE MISTAKE

37:27.570 --> 37:30.835
OF ASKING HER FRIEND
DEBORAH HAUSER FOR ADVICE.

37:30.840 --> 37:33.308
SO, WHEN
THE FUTURE HEALTH TEACHER

37:33.310 --> 37:35.574
SPREAD THE STORY
ALL OVER SCHOOL,

37:35.580 --> 37:38.549
THEY GOT CALLED INTO
THE PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE.

37:38.550 --> 37:40.984
SO, DID THEY NAIL
MY MYSTERY DAD?

37:40.990 --> 37:44.528
NOPE. MOM RECANTED, SAID SHE
MADE THE WHOLE THING UP.

37:44.530 --> 37:45.485
WHY?

37:45.490 --> 37:47.788
'CAUSE MARY BEGGED HER
NOT TO TELL.

37:47.790 --> 37:50.497
SHE DIDN'T WANT THE STORY
BEING CONFIRMED.

37:50.500 --> 37:53.196
SO SHE WANTED TO PROTECT
THE TEACHER?

37:53.200 --> 37:56.237
MARY WAS SCARED
AND PREGNANT.

37:56.240 --> 37:58.128
SO SHE DECIDED
IT WOULD BE EASIER

37:58.140 --> 37:59.539
TO JUST DUMP ME
AT THE PROM?

37:59.540 --> 38:01.337
NO, SHE LEFT YOU ON
YOUR FATHER'S DOORSTEP.

38:01.340 --> 38:03.331
HE WAS THE ONE
WHO PANICKED,

38:03.340 --> 38:05.149
KNOWING HE COULDN'T TAKE YOU
TO THE HOSPITAL

38:05.150 --> 38:06.549
WITHOUT
DRAWING SUSPICION.

38:06.550 --> 38:08.245
THE DANCE WAS PERFECT.

38:08.250 --> 38:11.276
EVERYONE WOULD ASSUME THE BABY
BELONGED TO A STUDENT.

38:11.280 --> 38:12.884
SO, WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY REAL DAD?

38:12.890 --> 38:14.949
YOU SAID HE WAS A TEACHER,
RIGHT?

38:14.960 --> 38:16.951
EVEN BETTER.

38:16.960 --> 38:19.554
RAISE ACADEMIC
ACHIEVEMENT SCORES.

38:19.560 --> 38:23.348
HEY, POPS.
HOPE I'M INTERRUPTING.

38:23.360 --> 38:25.066
TRINA, GLAD TO SEE
YOU'RE FEELING BETTER.

38:25.070 --> 38:26.867
I'D HEARD
THAT YOU WERE --
AT DEATH'S DOOR?

38:26.870 --> 38:29.293
AND WHEN EXACTLY WERE YOU
PLANNING TO HOOK ME UP

38:29.300 --> 38:30.631
WITH A LITTLE
BONE MARROW?

38:30.640 --> 38:32.267
PERHAPS WE SHOULD
TAKE THIS OUTSIDE.

38:32.270 --> 38:34.602
OH, COME ON, DAD.

38:34.610 --> 38:36.976
IT'S THE LEAST YOU CAN DO
FOR YOUR DAUGHTER

38:36.980 --> 38:39.778
AFTER DUMPING ME IN THE JOHN
ON PROM NIGHT.

38:43.820 --> 38:44.844
HEY.

38:45.990 --> 38:47.116
YOU GRAB DINNER YET?

38:47.120 --> 38:49.657
FUNNY YOU SHOULD ASK.

38:49.660 --> 38:51.480
I'M NOT ACTUALLY
THAT HUNGRY.

38:51.490 --> 38:53.981
I WAS SCROUNGING
THROUGH THE OLD FRIDGE

38:53.990 --> 38:55.491
FOR A LITTLE
STUDY SNACK.

38:55.500 --> 38:58.060
AND I'M NOT NORMALLY
A CORN DOG TYPE OF GIRL...

38:58.060 --> 39:00.426
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:00.430 --> 39:02.193
...BUT THIS...

39:02.200 --> 39:05.408
IS GONNA PUT ME OFF THEM
FOREVER.

39:05.410 --> 39:07.435
ARE YOU KEEPING A DEAD RAT
IN OUR FREEZER

39:07.440 --> 39:09.305
OR DO WE HAVE
A SLAM-DUNK LAWSUIT

39:09.310 --> 39:11.198
AGAINST THE
PROCESSED-FOOD INDUSTRY?

39:11.210 --> 39:12.609
I FOUND IT ON THE BUS.

39:12.610 --> 39:14.749
YOU CHECKED OUT THE BUS
AND DIDN'T TELL ME?

39:14.750 --> 39:19.346
IT WAS DUCT -TAPED
UNDER ONE OF THE BACK SEATS.

39:19.350 --> 39:23.013
IT WAS A MESSAGE FOR ME.
I'M THE RAT.

39:23.020 --> 39:24.658
I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE.

39:24.660 --> 39:26.821
MAYBE IT WAS SOMEONE ELSE
ON THE BUS.

39:28.430 --> 39:31.422
YOU WERE RIGHT,
VERONICA.

39:31.430 --> 39:33.022
I SHOULD'VE WON
THAT ELECTION.

39:33.030 --> 39:35.533
I SHOULD'VE
TAKEN OVER THIS CASE.

39:41.940 --> 39:43.703
YOU SLY, OLD DOG.

39:43.710 --> 39:46.076
YOUR SENTENCE IS UP, VERONICA,
UNLESS YOU'RE HERE

39:46.080 --> 39:48.640
TO ATONE FOR SOMETHING
I DON'T YET KNOW ABOUT.

39:48.650 --> 39:51.175
DEDUCING I HAD A KEY
TO YOUR OFFICE --

39:51.180 --> 39:52.886
NOW, THAT WAS CLEVER.

39:52.890 --> 39:55.779
OBVIOUSLY YOU HAD TO FIND A WAY
TO STICK ME IN DETENTION.

39:55.790 --> 39:58.452
THAT WAY YOU COULD BE SURE
I'D FIND MY WAY

39:58.460 --> 40:00.325
INTO MY MOM'S
PERMANENT FILE.

40:00.330 --> 40:02.525
WHAT ARE YOU
GOING ON ABOUT?

40:02.530 --> 40:06.398
YOU READ MACHIAVELLI
THIS SUMMER, DIDN'T YOU.

40:07.500 --> 40:09.092
OOH, NICE.

40:09.100 --> 40:12.308
NOT TAKING CREDIT FOR IT?

40:12.310 --> 40:13.709
EVEN MORE BADASS.

40:13.710 --> 40:15.678
THAT'S A VERY IMAGINATIVE
THEORY, VERONICA.

40:15.680 --> 40:20.572
BUT IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I'VE GOT A LOT OF PAPERWORK.

40:29.760 --> 40:32.786
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

40:34.860 --> 40:35.849
HELLO?

40:35.860 --> 40:37.259
Woman:
Hello, Ms. Mars?

40:37.260 --> 40:39.626
This is the Neptune
memorial hospital again

40:39.630 --> 40:42.167
regarding Abel Koontz's
belongings.

40:57.780 --> 40:59.543
HOW SOBERING IS IT

40:59.550 --> 41:03.384
THAT THE SUM OF A PERSON'S LIFE
FITS INTO A CARDBOARD BOX?

41:03.390 --> 41:06.052
SINCE I'VE MADE IT PAST
SECURITY ALREADY,

41:06.060 --> 41:08.426
THERE'S ONE THING
I WANT TO CHECK...

41:08.430 --> 41:11.695
MEG'S ROOM, UNGUARDED.

41:11.700 --> 41:13.861
[ HEART MONITOR BEEPING ]
